147	phmso0f3smcj4it6r8fdc5x8	A total of 226 medical students participated in the ECOE test at the La Paz University Hospital	On May 11 and 12, the La Paz University Hospital hosted the Structured Objective Clinical Examination (ECOE) test. Through standardized practical situations, the clinical competencies, communication skills, and techniques and skills of 6th year medical students at the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM) were evaluated.	2024-05-13	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Last weekend, La Paz University Hospital hosted the practical test of the Objective Structured Clinical Examination (ECOE) to assess the techniques and skills of students in the final year of the Medicine Degree , in which 226 students from the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM) took part.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The Dean of the Faculty, Pilar Lpez Garca, thanked the Technical, Management, Administration and Services Staff (PTGAS) involved in the test for their efforts and dedication, the work of the actors, evaluators and teachers and the excellent coordination of the professor and delegate of the Clinical Teaching Unit of the La Paz Hospital,   Manuel Quintana.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "She also had words of thanks for the Education Department of the Community of Madrid, for the Government Team of the UAM, represented by its Vice-Rector for Students, Javier Oubia, and for the President of the Social Council, Eduardo Sicilia, for their support on such an important day for the Faculty.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Authorities attending the ECOE test at the La Paz University Hospital last weekend. / UAM", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The ECOE consists of exposing students to a well-studied and delimited clinical situation that takes place in a simulated environment that recreates clinical realities. Each of these standardized situations is called a Station and can be a standardized patient (with actors), a mannequin (high, medium and low fidelity) or a chair (images and diagnostic tests), as explained by the test organizers. The stations are carried out for 10 minutes (2 of reading the initial situation and 8 of solving the clinical situation posed).", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "In this year's tests, a total of 12 stations were held simultaneously in the Outpatient Clinic area of the hospital. In order to assess the 226 6th year medical students, three simultaneous sessions of 36 stations were organised during three consecutive shifts.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "More than two hundred people have participated, as in previous editions, to ensure the success of this mandatory test for obtaining the Degree.", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-21 12:09:58.846	2024-11-26 19:42:41.241	2024-11-26 19:42:41.257	2	1	en	UAM students who participated in the ECOE test at the La Paz University Hospital last weekend. / J. Oubia-UAM
3	qno7xomn7cwdmd1ztcevbk0j	The UAM Employment Forum celebrates its 20th edition with the participation of more than 75 exhibitors	Until next Friday, March 15, the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM) is holding this annual meeting on employability. An event that will allow students and recent graduates to explore professional opportunities and establish contacts with companies from various sectors, including STEM. It will be held in a hybrid format and the physical venues will be the Faculty of Economic and Business Sciences and the Higher Polytechnic School (EPS).	2024-03-11	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://www.uam.es/uam/oficina-practicas-externas/empleo/foro-empleo", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "20th Employment Forum of the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM)", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": " will take place throughout this week - until next Friday, March 15 - in a hybrid format. The most important annual event with entrepreneurship at the UAM, organized by the Vice-Rectorate for Students and Employability of the UAM, celebrates its twentieth edition, which consolidates the success of the initiative, with the participation of more than 75 public and private entities. Its stands will be installed in the halls of the ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://www.uam.es/Economicas/Home.htm", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Faculty of Business Economics", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": " and the ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://www.uam.es/ss/Satellite/EscuelaPolitecnica/es/home.htm", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Higher Polytechnic School (EPS)", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": " on March 11 and 12. In parallel, from Wednesday 13 to Friday 15, the forum will have its virtual version in which you can participate by registering ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://foroempleouam.easyvirtualfair.com/home", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "at this link", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": " .  ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Image of the XX UAM Employment Forum at the Faculty of Economics and Business. / UAM", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "During the opening day, held today, the Vice-Rector for Students and Employability Javier Oubia, the Rector's Delegate for Employability and Alumni Idoia Alarcn and the Head of Service of the Internship and Employability Office Ruth Garca Aldea, toured the facilities, accompanied, in the Faculty of Economic and Business Sciences, by the Vice-Manager of Studies Cristina Soto and the Vice-Dean of Employability Mar Alonso (in the image).", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Access ", "type": "text"}, {"bold": true, "text": "to the Employment Forum is free and open ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "to anyone who comes to the Cantoblanco Campus on March 11 and 12. However, ", "type": "text"}, {"bold": true, "text": "some activities are exclusively aimed at UAM members", "type": "text"}, {"text": " , that is, currently enrolled students and AlumniUAM members. You can consult the complete program here .", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "This forum, which includes training activities, presentations and round tables in both modalities, offers students the opportunity to establish contacts with leading employers in various sectors, especially STEM, explore employment options to start their professional career and learn about the offer of internships and programs for graduates. The meeting also allows attendees to learn about the latest trends in the labor market and strategies for conducting an effective job search.  ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Featured Activities", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Image of the XX UAM Employment Forum at the Faculty of Economics and Business. / UAM", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Among the scheduled activities is the ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://foroempleouam.easyvirtualfair.com/resources/private/documents/Cafes_con_candidatos.pdf", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Student and Graduate Caf", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": ", an opportunity to network with human resources representatives from the different entities that will participate in the Employment Forum. At this unique event, upon registration, students will be able to establish relationships with Human Resources representatives from various entities participating in the Employment Forum. This caf is intended to take place in a relaxed but professional environment, designed to foster meaningful conversations and genuine connections. At the caf, students will be able to learn about internships or job opportunities available, expand their professional networks, and enjoy a welcoming and stimulating environment in the company of other UAM students and graduates with common affinities.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Participants will also be able to participate in the practical workshop ", "type": "text"}, {"bold": true, "text": "Learn to use LinkedIn", "type": "text"}, {"text": " and take advantage of the opportunity to boost their professional career on social networks. For 50 minutes, participants will immerse themselves in the world of LinkedIn, to understand how it works, master the techniques to build a profile and maximize their presence on this platform, expand their network of contacts and define their personal brand effectively.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The session is scheduled for  ", "type": "text"}, {"bold": true, "text": "Wednesday, March 13 at 12 noon", "type": "text"}, {"text": " in the Multifunction Room of the Faculty of Economics and Business Administration. Free admission.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The UAM and employability", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Image of the XX UAM Employment Forum at the Faculty of Economics and Business. / UAM", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The main objective of the XX Employment Forum is to promote the employability of students and graduates of the university. According to the latest data from the ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://obs-empleabilidad.uam.es/", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "UAM Employment Observatory ", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": ", 8 out of 10 graduates of Bachelor's degrees, 9 out of 10 Master's and Own Degrees and 10 out of 10 Doctorate graduates enter the labour market. The average time of active search for recent graduates who had not previously worked is between two and three months. The data also reflect that around 80% of graduates of Bachelor's degrees, postgraduate degrees and doctorates consider that the UAM has contributed to improving their employability.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "The Forum in detail", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Date:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "March 11 and 12 from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. (in-person format). March 13, 14 and 15 ( online format ).", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Hour:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "From 10 am to 6 pm", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Place:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Face-to-face Employment Forum: Entrance hall to the Faculty of Economics and Business Administration and entrance hall to the Higher Polytechnic School (EPS). Cantoblanco Campus.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://foroempleouam.easyvirtualfair.com/landing", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Virtual Employment Forum", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://www.uam.es/uam/oficina-practicas-externas/empleo/foro-empleo", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "More information", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": "", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-18 20:50:15.931	2024-11-26 19:26:25.883	\N	1	1	en	Poster of the XX UAM Employment Forum at the Faculty of Economics and Business. / UAM
7	bsqd5j0vdajumkhwzg9wv0tn	The UAM hosts the presentation of the Crue-RUEPEP guide for the preparation of microcredentials	During the session, the common criteria established in the document 'Guidelines for the design and accreditation of university micro-credentials', prepared by CRUE-RUEPEP, were revealed. These types of qualifications are focused on the development of specific professional skills and meet the current needs of the labour market.\n\n	2024-03-11	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The Auditorium of the", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://www.uam.es/Profesorado/Home.htm", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": " Faculty of Teacher Training and Education of the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM)", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": " was the setting for the presentation of the document ", "type": "text"}, {"bold": true, "text": "Guidelines for the design and accreditation of university microcredentials", "type": "text"}, {"text": ", prepared by three Crue-RUEPEP working groups (Quality, Microcredentials and Employment) which are also made up of those responsible for postgraduate studies and continuing education from more than 30 Spanish universities, both public and private.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Isabel Alonso, Vice-Rector for Postgraduate Studies and Continuing Education, welcomed the attendees and introduced the participants in the panel, which was made up of Nicols Rodriguez Garca, Vice-Rector for Postgraduate Studies and Own Courses at the University of Salamanca; Mara Valds Gzquez, Rector's Commissioner for the Postgraduate School and Teaching Quality at the University of Barcelona; Sandra Marcos, Director of the Technical Quality Unit at the Pontifical University of Salamanca; Jon Altuna, Academic Vice-Rector at the University of Mondragn; Vanesa Valero, Vice-Rector for Continuing Education at the University of Murcia; Mara Jos Gonzlez, Vice-Rector for Own Courses and Distance Learning at the University of Cantabria; Margalida Furi, Director of UIBTalent Advanced Training at the University-Business Foundation of the Balearic Islands; and Santiago Gutirrez, Vice-Rector for Postgraduate and Continuing Education at the University of Castilla-La Mancha.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Throughout the session, the members have addressed each of the axes that articulate the document, focusing on the fundamental aspects that correspond to the elaboration, development and accreditation of microcredentials such as the design and certification of the elements that compose them, the qualification levels, quality assurance, the promotion of visibility, the need to implement a national program, its role in training for employment in the workplace, and the introduction of mechanisms that allow it to be employment-oriented training.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The challenges faced by university micro-credentials within the social context were also present during the conference. Among them, the following were highlighted: bureaucratization, the incorporation of technologies, synergies between universities and administrations, the specialization and motivation of the teaching staff, the detection of training needs with stable structures and the connection with companies, among others.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "The UAM and the RUEPEP Network", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://ruepep.org/", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "The RUEPEP Network ", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": "(University Network of Postgraduate Studies and Continuing Education) is an association that includes Spanish public and private universities, including the UAM, since 2010, the year the Network was founded.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The main objective of the RUEPEP Network is to promote contact between Spanish universities on the specific subject of postgraduate studies and continuing education, both from an academic point of view and from that of their specialized management.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-18 21:00:02.372	2024-11-26 19:31:59.337	\N	1	1	en	Isabel Alonso, Vice-Rector for Postgraduate Studies and Continuing Education at the UAM, together with the panel of participants at the presentation of the document.
