resenting the entities were Enrique Celma, Director of Business Development for the Digital Agenda; Agustn Gallego, Director of Public Administration and Business Markets; and Juan-Pablo Ferrero, Director of Western Europe at the Intel Global Education Center of Excellence.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The UAM-Intel-Genially Chair, directed by Professor Melchor Gmez, is based on learning experiences created by Intel in its Intel Skills for Innovation program supported by the Genially gamification experience creation tool, and aims to promote teaching, research, development and innovation in the field of digital teaching competence, since they benefit from possible advances in these areas and the dissemination of specialized knowledge to researchers and professionals. All this through the implementation of related postgraduate teaching activities both in Doctorate Programs and in Master's degrees and Expert or Specialization Diplomas; facilitate the professional insertion of students from the Autonomous University of Madrid and promote collaboration between the Autonomous University of Madrid and the business sector.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The Chair will focus on the research, development and promotion of technological and educational solutions aimed at improving the educational experience both in the university environment and in education in general. This joint effort will allow the creation of advanced academic programs, the carrying out of pioneering research, and the organization of outreach and training activities aimed at the university community.", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-18 22:49:30.718	2024-11-26 19:37:30.547	\N	1	1	en	\N
