ps://www.uam.es/uam/derecho", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Grado en Derecho", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": "). Su entrenadora fue ", "type": "text"}, {"bold": true, "text": "Carmen Martnez Capdevila", "type": "text"}, {"text": ", profesora titular del ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://www.uam.es/ss/Satellite/Derecho/es/1234889450599/subhome/Area_de_Derecho_Internacional_Publico.htm", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "rea de Derecho Internacional Pblico", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": " en la UAM.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "En esta edicin participaron 18 equipos procedentes de facultades de Derecho de universidades pblicas y privadas de toda Espaa. A finales de enero se conocieron los 12 equipos que, por haber presentado unos mejores escritos, pasaban a la fase oral de la competicin, consistente en la reproduccin de una vista ante el Tribunal de Justicia de la UE en las sedes del Consejo General de la Abogaca y del Tribunal Supremo.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "En primera ronda, el equipo de la UAM se enfrent a las Universidades de Alcal de Henares (donde actu como demandado) y de Castilla-La Mancha (donde asumi el papel de demandante). En la semifinal superaron a la Universidad de Deusto y, en la final, celebrada en la sala de plenos del Tribunal Supremo, se impusieron a la Universidad de Zaragoza.", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-18 22:55:10.773	2024-11-26 19:41:21.718	\N	1	1	es	El equipo formado por Yocandra Martnez Martnez, Juan Milln de Meer, Luisa Aragn Lpez y Dino Briatore Najmias, con su entrenadora Carmen Martnez Capdevila, en la sala de plenos del Tribunal Supremo. / Foto cedida por sus autores
38	cmo7skiwqv9v07550cm981ek	A team from the Faculty of Law, champion of the 3rd edition of the 'Moot Court AEDEUR'	\nYocandra Martnez Martnez, Juan Milln de Meer, Luisa Aragn Lpez and Dino Briatore Najmias, with the advice of their coach Professor Carmen Martnez Capdevila, were the winners of this edition of the 'AEDEUR Moot Court', a university competition to promote the study of European Law in Spain.	2024-03-22	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "On March 15, a team of students from the Faculty of Law of the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM) was proclaimed champion of the 3rd edition of the ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://www.aedeur.es/", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "AEDEUR Moot Court ", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": ", in the field of European Union (EU) Law. This university competition is based on a simulated trial and is aimed at students of the Degree in Law or Double Degrees with Law from Spanish universities. Its objective is to promote interest in this area of study and this specialty among university students.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The team was made up of ", "type": "text"}, {"bold": true, "text": "Yocandra Martnez Martnez", "type": "text"}, {"text": " (4th year of the ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://www.uam.es/uam/en/noticias/Doble%20Grado%20en%20Derecho%20y%20Ciencia%20Pol%C3%ADtica", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Double Degree in Law and Political Science", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": " ), J", "type": "text"}, {"bold": true, "text": "uan Milln de Meer", "type": "text"}, {"text": " (4th year of ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://www.uam.es/uam/derecho", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "the Degree in Law", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": " ), Luisa Aragn Lpez and Dino Briatore Najmias (both 3rd year of ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://www.uam.es/uam/derecho", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "the Degree in Law", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": " ). Their coach was Carmen Martnez Capdevila, a professor in the ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://www.uam.es/ss/Satellite/Derecho/es/1234889450599/subhome/Area_de_Derecho_Internacional_Publico.htm", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Department of Public International Law at the UAM.", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Eighteen teams from law schools at public and private universities throughout Spain participated in this edition. At the end of January, the 12 teams that had submitted the best written submissions were announced and went on to the oral phase of the competition, which consisted of the reproduction of a hearing before the Court of Justice of the EU at the headquarters of the General Council of the Legal Profession and the Supreme Court.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "In the first round, the UAM team faced the Universities of Alcal de Henares (where it acted as defendant) and Castilla-La Mancha (where it assumed the role of plaintiff). In the semi-final they beat the University of Deusto and, in the final, held in the plenary hall of the Supreme Court, they beat the University of Zaragoza.", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-18 22:58:25.629	2024-11-26 19:41:46.972	\N	1	1	en	The team formed by Yocandra Martnez Martnez, Juan Milln de Meer, Luisa Aragn Lpez and Dino Briatore Najmias, with their coach Carmen Martnez Capdevila, in the plenary hall of the Supreme Court. / Photo provided by its authors
42	n7izoby6us1fyc7t4rvcoizn	UAM and APADIS sign an agreement for the development of Service Learning projects	The alliance between both institutions represents a commitment to promoting joint actions aimed at an education that is closer to the principles of social responsibility and the inclusion of people with disabilities in the university community.	2024-03-22	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM) and APADIS have signed an agreement to carry out Service-Learning (SLL) projects that promote values of solidarity, social justice, commitment and respect among students through their participation in actions with vulnerable groups.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The document, which is valid for four years, reflects the UAM's commitment to link the academic training of its students with social values, establishing the number of students participating in each project and recognizing the corresponding academic credits for their participation. In addition, the UAM undertakes to provide civil liability insurance for all students who participate in any of the projects.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "As regards APADIS, the association agrees on the conditions for student participation and designates a contact person to monitor the projects in order to provide all the information necessary for the correct performance of the activities, as well as to respect the rights and duties of the students, and to collaborate in the evaluation of the project for its improvement.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The signing took place at the APADIS headquarters and was attended by the Vice-Rector for Undergraduate Studies, Santiago Palacios, and Mara Luisa Santos, UAM advisor for Learning and Service, on behalf of the UAM. On behalf of APADIS, Jos Luis Tornos, Honorary President; Miguel ngel Jimnez, General Director; Laura Galindo, Director of the Employment Area; and Iago Armesto, representative of people with disabilities, participated.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "With this alliance, both institutions seek to promote values of solidarity, social justice, commitment and respect, giving students the opportunity to apply their knowledge for the benefit of society and thus contributing to the construction of a more inclusive and sustainable world.", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-18 23:01:50.174	2024-11-26 19:35:26.953	\N	1	1	en	Vice-rector for Undergraduate Studies Santiago Palacios (right) visits the APADIS facilities together with Mara Luisa Santos, UAM Learning and Service Advisor
