101	cr2vifxbqbzxl8l7rxy9kifs	The UAM and the ONCE Foundation sign an agreement to improve equal opportunities for people with disabilities in the university community	The rector Amaya Mendikoetxea and the general director of the ONCE Foundation, Jos Luis Martnez Donoso, have signed a framework agreement for collaboration to implement measures and promote initiatives aimed at improving equal opportunities, universal accessibility, inclusion and non-discrimination of people with disabilities within the university community, also promoting socially responsible public procurement.	2024-07-09	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM) and the ONCE Foundation have joined forces once again to strengthen their capacity for action and improve equal opportunities for people with disabilities in the university community.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The rector Amaya Mendikoetxea and the general director of the ONCE Foundation, Jos Luis Martnez Donoso, signed today at the Rectorate of the UAM a framework agreement for collaboration to implement measures and promote initiatives aimed at improving equal opportunities, universal accessibility, inclusion and non-discrimination of all people with disabilities, also promoting socially responsible public procurement (in the image, below these lines).", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The rector Amaya Mendikoetxea and the general director of the ONCE Foundation, Jos Luis Martnez Donoso, sign the agreement. On the left, the vice-rector Marta Morgade. / UAM", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "This agreement, which will last four years, also includes other specific collaboration agreements and/or educational cooperation agreements with other external entities and companies that are interested in sharing the objectives and programs to be developed.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The event was attended by, on behalf of the UAM, the Vice-Rector for Social Commitment and Sustainability, Marta Morgade (in the photo, with the Rector and the Director of the ONCE Foundation) ; the Vice-Rector for Students and Employability, Javier Oubia; the Vice-Rector for Postgraduate Studies and Continuing Education, Isabel Alonso; the Director of Projects at the UAM, Ana Caro; the Director of Continuing Education, Luis Jos Unceta; the Director of Cultural Activities at the UAM, Sandra Senz-Lpez ; the Rector's Delegate for Equity; Mnica Desire Snchez ; and the Functional Diversity technicians from the UAM Equity Unit, Eva Acedo and Andrea Calvo.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "On behalf of the ONCE Foundation, in addition to its general director, the director of Programs with Universities and Promotion of Young Talent, Isabel Martnez; the director of Accessibility and Innovation, Jess Hernndez; the head of the Department of Programs with Universities and Promotion of Young Talent, Silvia Duarte; the director of the Program For Digital Talent, Mnica Cadenas; and the technician of Programs with Universities and Promotion of Young Talent, Romn Muoz, attended.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Areas of action", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "This agreement signed between the UAM and Fundacin ONCE is based on the commitment to achieve Sustainable Development Goal 4 (SDG4), which seeks to guarantee inclusive, equitable and quality education and promote lifelong learning opportunities for all people.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The main areas of action covered by the agreement are: Awareness, awareness and training; Universal Accessibility and design for all people; Promotion of equal opportunities for students with disabilities and their inclusion in the labour market; and the development of a Forum for socially responsible recruitment, among other aspects.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "In addition, a Monitoring Committee will be created to monitor and implement this agreement and to encourage and coordinate the actions of the signatory parties.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Thanks to this initiative, numerous actions can be carried out to better meet the needs and demands of people with disabilities in the university community and contribute to the removal of barriers to university study and inclusion in the world of work. Educational awareness will also be promoted and academic guidance programmes will be strengthened to take advantage of talent.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The UAM will also participate in the University Guide for Students with Disabilities developed by the ONCE Foundation and will promote research and studies related to equal opportunities, disability and universal accessibility and design for all people, as well as improving the quality of life of people with disabilities in collaboration with the foundation.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "For its part, the ONCE Foundation will provide basic and specific advice that can address the needs of the UAM in this area and in the design and development of Universal Accessibility Plans, among others.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "As regards the promotion of equal opportunities for students with disabilities and their inclusion in the labour market, they will facilitate access and participation in transnational mobility programmes by people with disabilities within the university community and participation in external academic internships, including the option of the ONCE Foundation as a host company for carrying out external academic internships. The Inserta Empleo Association may collaborate in the development of actions to improve the employability and labour inclusion of students and graduates with disabilities at the UAM .", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Likewise, the Autonomous University of Madrid will be part of the Forum for Socially Responsible Contracting, an initiative to create and maintain employment for people with disabilities, as well as universal accessibility through public contracting, which includes inclusive public and private entities.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The signatory parties have also expressed their interest in promoting the creation and approval of internal regulations governing the access of people with disabilities to teaching and research bodies, as well as administration and services of the University, applying, developing and specifying in their own regulations the current legislation on the reservation of public employment for people with disabilities. In addition, positive action measures will be established so that they can fully develop their professional careers.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "A moment during the signing of the UAM-ONCE Agreement at the Rectorate. / UAM", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "A solid relationship", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The Autonomous University of Madrid and the ONCE Foundation have been collaborating for decades to promote the inclusion of people with disabilities. The ONCE School of Physiotherapy has become a renowned university centre, especially since its association with the Autonomous University of Madrid three decades ago. In addition, the UAM participates in the 2023-2024 ONCE Foundation-Crue Scholarship Programme for Spanish Universities , managing the allocation of scholarships for students and has collaborated on other projects, such as the musical proposal Gian Andrea Doria and the music in the galleys of Felipe II for the 50th Cycle of Great Authors and Performers of Music of the Higher Centre for Research and Promotion of Music (CSIPM) in which the theatre and film actor belonging to the ONCE Theatre Movement Jos Manuel Gmez San Juan received great applause from the public.  ", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-21 12:22:43.563	2024-11-26 19:36:21.565	\N	2	1	en	Officials from the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM) and the ONCE Foundation, after signing the agreement at the Rector's Office. / UAM
