onsible recruitment, among other aspects.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "In addition, a Monitoring Committee will be created to monitor and implement this agreement and to encourage and coordinate the actions of the signatory parties.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Thanks to this initiative, numerous actions can be carried out to better meet the needs and demands of people with disabilities in the university community and contribute to the removal of barriers to university study and inclusion in the world of work. Educational awareness will also be promoted and academic guidance programmes will be strengthened to take advantage of talent.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The UAM will also participate in the University Guide for Students with Disabilities developed by the ONCE Foundation and will promote research and studies related to equal opportunities, disability and universal accessibility and design for all people, as well as improving the quality of life of people with disabilities in collaboration with the foundation.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "For its part, the ONCE Foundation will provide basic and specific advice that can address the needs of the UAM in this area and in the design and development of Universal Accessibility Plans, among others.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "As regards the promotion of equal opportunities for students with disabilities and their inclusion in the labour market, they will facilitate access and participation in transnational mobility programmes by people with disabilities within the university community and participation in external academic internships, including the option of the ONCE Foundation as a host company for carrying out external academic internships. The Inserta Empleo Association may collaborate in the development of actions to improve the employability and labour inclusion of students and graduates with disabilities at the UAM .", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Likewise, the Autonomous University of Madrid will be part of the Forum for Socially Responsible Contracting, an initiative to create and maintain employment for people with disabilities, as well as universal accessibility through public contracting, which includes inclusive public and private entities.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The signatory parties have also expressed their interest in promoting the creation and approval of internal regulations governing the access of people with disabilities to teaching and research bodies, as well as administration and services of the University, applying, developing and specifying in their own regulations the current legislation on the reservation of public employment for people with disabilities. In addition, positive action measures will be established so that they can fully develop their professional careers.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "A moment during the signing of the UAM-ONCE Agreement at the Rectorate. / UAM", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "A solid relationship", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The Autonomous University of Madrid and the ONCE Foundation have been collaborating for decades to promote the inclusion of people with disabilities. The ONCE School of Physiotherapy has become a renowned university centre, especially since its association with the Autonomous University of Madrid three decades ago. In addition, the UAM participates in the 2023-2024 ONCE Foundation-Crue Scholarship Programme for Spanish Universities , managing the allocation of scholarships for students and has collaborated on other projects, such as the musical proposal Gian Andrea Doria and the music in the galleys of Felipe II for the 50th Cycle of Great Authors and Performers of Music of the Higher Centre for Research and Promotion of Music (CSIPM) in which the theatre and film actor belonging to the ONCE Theatre Movement Jos Manuel Gmez San Juan received great applause from the public.  ", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-21 12:22:43.563	2024-11-26 19:36:21.565	2024-11-26 19:36:21.582	2	1	en	Officials from the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM) and the ONCE Foundation, after signing the agreement at the Rector's Office. / UAM
