", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The new director of the EPS, Carlos Aguirre Maeso, graduated in Sciences (Mathematics) from the UAM in 1989 and received his PhD in Computer Science from the same university in 2002. From 1989 to 2000 he worked as an analyst at the Institute for Knowledge Engineering (IIC). He has been a visiting professor at the Institute for Nonlinear Science (San Diego, USA), Zentrum fur Interdisciplinare Forschung (Bielefeld, Germany) and Complexo Interdisiplinar da Universidade de Lisboa (Lisbon, Portugal). He is currently a contracted professor with a PhD in the Department of Computer Engineering at the UAM. His main areas of interest are the analysis and study of complex networks, the analysis and study of biological signals, the development of tools for data analysis and the study of atmospheric phenomena on Mars. He has published more than 30 articles in international journals and has participated in more than 20 national and international research projects. Dialogue, support for research, fostering talent, improving teaching quality and encouraging student participation are some of the challenges for this new stage.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "More information", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-21 11:34:53.731	2024-11-26 19:29:54.65	\N	2	1	en	The general secretary, Alma Rodrguez; the rector Amaya Mendikoetxea;
57	qqehiouffbiocygp9dn0e4ag	La Ctedra UAM-EducAccin abre nuevos horizontes en la innovacin y el enfoque ESG en el mbito educativo	La Ctedra UAM-EducAccin, presentada ayer, tiene por objetivo trazar nuevos caminos hacia una educacin ms justa, equitativa y sostenible y medir el impacto en las reas ambiental, social y de gobernanza. Ser una plataforma para discutir y promover nuevas orientaciones para un mejor Sistema Educativo en Espaa.	2024-04-04	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "La ", "type": "text"}, {"url": " http://www.uam.es/", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Universidad Autnoma de Madrid (UAM)", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": " y ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://www.educaccion.org/", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "EducAccin", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": " se han unido para impulsar la innovacin y el impacto social, medioambiental y de gobernanza (Enviromental, Social y Governance, ESG) en el mbito educativo. Este esfuerzo conjunto se ha materializado en la Ctedra EducAccin en Impacto Ambiental, Social y de Gobernanza en el Sector Educativo, que tiene como objetivo fundamental trazar nuevos caminos hacia una educacin ms justa, equitativa y sostenible.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "El acto de presentacin, celebrado ayer, reuni a destacados lderes acadmicos y expertos en Educacin en nuestro pas. Asistieron el vicerrector de Transferencia, Innovacin y Cultura de la UAM, Flix Zamora; el director general de la FUAM, Fidel Rodrguez Batalla; el director de la ctedra, Santiago Atrio; la presidenta del Comit Cientfico de la ctedra, Sonia Dez; y el codirector de la ctedra, Jos Pic. El evento tambin cont con la presencia del filsofo y pedagogo Jos Antonio Marina y del presidente de la Fundacin Cultura de Paz, Federico Mayor Zaragoza, entre otras personalidades relevantes.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "La creacin de esta ctedra marca el comienzo de una nueva era en la educacin y se presenta como una plataforma para discutir y promover nuevas orientaciones para el futuro de este importante motor social.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Desde la Universidad Autnoma de Madrid hasta las instituciones y empresas colaboradoras, todos se han unido en este esfuerzo conjunto para redefinir el papel de la educacin en la sociedad. Desde su organizacin, se invita cordialmente a participar en este debate crucial a todas aquellas personas comprometidas con el futuro del aprendizaje y el bienestar de las generaciones venideras.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "En palabras de Sonia Dez, presidenta del Comit Cientfico de la ctedra: En un mundo donde la calidad educativa se ha medido tradicionalmente por parmetros acadmicos, la Ctedra EducAccin propone una visin revolucionaria. La calidad de la educacin va ms all de las calificaciones de los estudiantes y debe medirse por su impacto en las reas ambiental, social y de gobernanza.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Al adoptar el enfoque de \\"doble materialidad\\" en su reporting anual, la educacin se alinea con estndares internacionales de otros sectores, lo que permite una evaluacin ms holstica de su verdadero valor y costo. Esta iniciativa pionera busca destacar el coste de oportunidad de una educacin deficiente y promover prcticas que contribuyan a un sistema educativo ms slido y sostenible.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://fuam.es/catedras/", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Ms informacin ", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": "", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-21 11:24:47.849	2024-11-26 19:30:35.09	\N	2	1	es	Los responsables de la Ctedra UAM-EducAccin, tras el acto de presentacin. 
59	qqehiouffbiocygp9dn0e4ag	The UAM-EducAccin Chair opens new horizons in innovation and the ESG approach in the educational field	The UAM-EducAccin Chair, launched yesterday, aims to chart new paths towards a more just, equitable and sustainable education and to measure the impact in the environmental, social and governance areas. It will be a platform to discuss and promote new directions for a better Educational System in Spain.	2024-04-04	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM) and EducAccin have joined forces to promote innovation and social, environmental and governance ( ESG) impact in the educational field. This joint effort has materialized in the EducAccin Chair in Environmental, Social and Governance Impact in the Education Sector, which has the fundamental objective of charting new paths towards a more just, equitable and sustainable education.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The presentation ceremony, held yesterday, brought together prominent academic leaders and experts in Education in our country. The event was attended by the Vice-Rector for Transfer, Innovation and Culture of the UAM, Flix Zamora; the General Director of the FUAM, Fidel Rodrguez Batalla; the Director of the Chair, Santiago Atrio; the President of the Scientific Committee of the Chair, Sonia Dez; and the Co-Director of the Chair, Jos Pic. The event was also attended by the philosopher and pedagogue Jos Antonio Marina and the President of the Culture of Peace Foundation, Federico Mayor Zaragoza, among other relevant personalities.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The creation of this chair marks the beginning of a new era in education and is presented as a platform to discuss and promote new directions for the future of this important social engine.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "From the Autonomous University of Madrid to the collaborating institutions and companies, everyone has joined in this joint effort to redefine the role of education in society. The organization cordially invites all those committed to the future of learning and the well-being of future generations to participate in this crucial debate.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "In the words of Sonia Dez, president of the Chair's Scientific Committee: In a world where educational quality has traditionally been measured by academic parameters, the EducAccin Chair proposes a revolutionary vision. The quality of education goes beyond student grades and must be measured by its impact on the environmental, social and governance areas . ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "By adopting a dual materiality approach in its annual reporting , education is aligned with international standards for other sectors, allowing for a more holistic assessment of its true value and cost. This pioneering initiative seeks to highlight the opportunity cost of poor education and promote practices that contribute to a stronger and more sustainable education system.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "More information ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-21 11:26:15.384	2024-11-26 19:31:00.566	\N	2	1	en	The heads of the UAM-EducAccin Chair, after the presentation ceremony. 
67	cgbcwjc3h4cl79xv1e78ctpu	UAM places seven areas in the world top 100 of the 'QS Ranking by Subject 2024'	The Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM) has improved its ranking by subject area by ranking among the 100 best universities in the world in seven of them, according to the 'QS By Subject Ranking 2024'. Regarding the macro-areas, Natural Sciences obtains the best rating, ranking 85th in the table, followed by Social Sciences, Arts and Humanities, Health Sciences and Medicine (all of them among the 200 best in the world) and Engineering and Technology (which improves by 20 points compared to the previous edition).	2024-04-10	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM) maintains its good results in the five macro-areas analysed by the QS by Subject Ranking 2024 published today and is ranked in 36 of the 45 areas evaluated in this classification. In addition, it places its areas of Physics, History, Anthropology, Law, Modern Languages, Education and Psychology in the top 100 in the world.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "As for the macro-areas analysed, Natural Sciences obtains the best rating , ranking 85th in the table, followed by Social Sciences, Arts and Humanities, Health Sciences and Medicine (all of them among the 200 best in the world) and Engineering and Technology (which improves by 20 points compared to the previous edition).", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Of the 36 areas in which the UAM is classified, our institution achieves a position in the top 100 in 7 of them, making this edition the one that includes more areas in that segment than the last four editions.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "With this ranking, the UAM strengthens its excellent position at an international level: it is one of the 100 best European universities according to the QS World University Rankings: Europe 2024 , it is among the 200 best in the world in sustainability and among the most transparent universities in Spain . Nearly a hundred of its researchers are considered among the most influential in the world according to the Stanford Top 2% Scientists Ranking.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The 14th edition of the QS World University Rankings by Subject provides an independent comparative analysis of the performance of more than 16,400 individual university programmes, pursued by students at over 1,500 institutions in 96 locations around the world, 55 academic disciplines and five major areas of study .", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "More information", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-21 11:39:25.192	2024-11-26 19:34:24.589	\N	2	1	en	\N
