141	xdb61q3wq6a8o5zpaywfvlj6	Neus Teixidor, researcher at the UAM Faculty of Law, receives the First Fernando Albi Prize on Local Administration	Neus Teixidor Martnez, PhD in Law from the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM), has been awarded the First Fernando Albi Prize 2023, convened by the Alicante Provincial Council, for her work 'The duality of management in the Property Tax: the impact of cadastral data on the management of the Property Tax'. This study is based on her doctoral thesis, defended last year, for which she also obtained an international mention and the highest grade awarded by the court.	2024-04-03	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Neus Teixidor Martnez ", "type": "text"}, {"text": ", PhD in Law from the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM), received on March 20 the", "type": "text"}, {"bold": true, "text": " First Fernando Albi Prize 2023 ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "convened by the Alicante Provincial Council for her work ", "type": "text"}, {"bold": true, "text": "The duality of management in the Real Estate Tax:", "type": "text"}, {"text": " the impact of cadastral data on the management of the Real Estate Tax. These prestigious awards were created in 1973 in order to promote the development of studies that highlight the Local Administration and the work carried out by its professionals. To this end, the scientific-technical quality, novelty, rigor of analysis, significance in the Local Administration, conclusions and personal contributions of the author are taken into account. The jury of the awards was made up of relevant members of the Administration, the Judiciary and the Academy.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "As explained by the", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://www.uam.es/Derecho/Home.htm", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": " UAM Faculty of Law", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": " , the winning work has its origin in the doctoral thesis defended in July 2023 by Teixidor, entitled ", "type": "text"}, {"bold": true, "text": "The problems arising from shared management in the Real Estate Tax", "type": "text"}, {"text": ", of which Domingo Jimnez-Valladolid, professor of Financial and Tax Law, was the director; and Juan Arrieta, professor of Financial and Tax Law, was the tutor. The thesis had an ", "type": "text"}, {"bold": true, "text": "international mention ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "and obtained the ", "type": "text"}, {"bold": true, "text": "highest grade", "type": "text"}, {"text": " awarded by the tribunal, composed of professors Diego Marn-Barnuevo (UAM), Juan Varona (University of Cantabria), Mara Luisa Esteve (University of Girona), Ricardo Garca (University of Tilburg) and Csar Martnez (UAM).", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://www.diputacionalicante.es/noticias/un-trabajo-sobre-la-dualidad-de-gestion-en-el-ibi-gana-los-premios-fernando-albi-que-convoca-la-diputacion/", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "More information", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": "", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-18 23:16:30.525	2024-11-26 19:39:20.689	2024-11-26 19:39:20.705	1	1	en	The winner of the Prize, Neus Teixidor, together with the president of the Alicante Provincial Council, Toni Prez
86	phmso0f3smcj4it6r8fdc5x8	Un total de 226 estudiantes de Medicina participan en la prueba ECOE en el Hospital Universitario La Paz	Los pasados das 11 y 12 de mayo, el Hospital Universitario La Paz acogi la prueba del Examen Clnico Objetivo Estructurado (ECOE). A travs de situaciones prcticas estandarizadas, se evaluaron las competencias clnicas, las habilidades comunicativas y las tcnicas y destrezas de los estudiantes de 6 de Medicina de la Universidad Autnoma de Madrid (UAM).	2024-05-13	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "El Hospital Universitario La Paz acogi el pasado fin de semana la prueba prctica de competencias del Examen Clnico Objetivo Estructurado (ECOE) para evaluar tcnicas y destrezas de los estudiantes del ltimo curso del Grado de Medicina, en la que tomaron parte 226 estudiantes de la Universidad Autnoma de Madrid (UAM).", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "La decana de la Facultad, Pilar Lpez Garca, agradeci el esfuerzo y la dedicacin del Personal Tcnico, de Gestin y de Administracin y Servicios (PTGAS) implicado en la prueba, la labor de los actores, evaluadores y docentes y la excelente coordinacin del profesor y delegado de la Unidad Clnica Docente del Hospital La Paz,  Manuel Quintana.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Tambin tuvo palabras de agradecimiento para la Consejera de Educacin de la Comunidad de Madrid, para el Equipo de Gobierno de la UAM, representado a travs de su vicerrector de Estudiantes, Javier Oubia, y para el presidente del Consejo Social, Eduardo Sicilia, por su apoyo en un da tan importante para la Facultad.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Autoridades asistentes a la prueba ECOE en Hospital Universitario La Paz el pasado fin de semana. / UAM", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "El ECOE consiste en exponer al estudiantado a una situacin clnica perfectamente estudiada y delimitada que se desarrolla en un ambiente simulado que recrea realidades clnicas. Cada una de estas situaciones estandarizadas se denomina Estacin y pueden ser de paciente estandarizados (con actores), de maniqu (de alta, media y baja fidelidad) o de silla (imgenes y pruebas diagnsticas), como explican los organizadores de la prueba. Las estaciones se realizan durante 10 minutos (2 de lectura de la situacin de partida y 8 de resolucin de la situacin clnica planteada).", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "En las pruebas de este ao, fueron un total de 12 estaciones las que se desarrollaron de forma simultnea en la zona de Consultas Externas del hospital. Para poder evaluar a los 226 estudiantes de 6 de Medicina, se organizaron tres ruedas simultneas de 36 estaciones durante tres turnos consecutivos.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Ms de doscientas personas han participado, como en ediciones anteriores, para garantizar el xito de esta prueba obligatoria para la obtencin del Grado.", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-21 12:07:49.905	2024-11-26 19:42:16.778	\N	2	1	es	Estudiantes de la UAM que participaron en la prueba ECOE en Hospital Universitario La Paz el pasado fin de semana. / J. Oubia-UAM
88	phmso0f3smcj4it6r8fdc5x8	A total of 226 medical students participated in the ECOE test at the La Paz University Hospital	On May 11 and 12, the La Paz University Hospital hosted the Structured Objective Clinical Examination (ECOE) test. Through standardized practical situations, the clinical competencies, communication skills, and techniques and skills of 6th year medical students at the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM) were evaluated.	2024-05-13	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Last weekend, La Paz University Hospital hosted the practical test of the Objective Structured Clinical Examination (ECOE) to assess the techniques and skills of students in the final year of the Medicine Degree , in which 226 students from the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM) took part.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The Dean of the Faculty, Pilar Lpez Garca, thanked the Technical, Management, Administration and Services Staff (PTGAS) involved in the test for their efforts and dedication, the work of the actors, evaluators and teachers and the excellent coordination of the professor and delegate of the Clinical Teaching Unit of the La Paz Hospital,   Manuel Quintana.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "She also had words of thanks for the Education Department of the Community of Madrid, for the Government Team of the UAM, represented by its Vice-Rector for Students, Javier Oubia, and for the President of the Social Council, Eduardo Sicilia, for their support on such an important day for the Faculty.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Authorities attending the ECOE test at the La Paz University Hospital last weekend. / UAM", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The ECOE consists of exposing students to a well-studied and delimited clinical situation that takes place in a simulated environment that recreates clinical realities. Each of these standardized situations is called a Station and can be a standardized patient (with actors), a mannequin (high, medium and low fidelity) or a chair (images and diagnostic tests), as explained by the test organizers. The stations are carried out for 10 minutes (2 of reading the initial situation and 8 of solving the clinical situation posed).", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "In this year's tests, a total of 12 stations were held simultaneously in the Outpatient Clinic area of the hospital. In order to assess the 226 6th year medical students, three simultaneous sessions of 36 stations were organised during three consecutive shifts.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "More than two hundred people have participated, as in previous editions, to ensure the success of this mandatory test for obtaining the Degree.", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-21 12:09:58.846	2024-11-26 19:42:41.241	\N	2	1	en	UAM students who participated in the ECOE test at the La Paz University Hospital last weekend. / J. Oubia-UAM
150	zo498sm1aoifbpcvxtk8a016	New mechanisms discovered in the immune synapse that could improve therapies against cancer and autoimmune diseases	Researchers from the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM) and the CSIC have discovered key processes in the immune synapse that open up new therapeutic possibilities for treating autoimmune diseases and improving the response of T lymphocytes to cancer. The breakthrough, published in eLife , could revolutionize the treatment of these diseases through targeted manipulation of the immune system.	2024-11-19	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "A Spanish team led by the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM) and the Spanish National Research Council (CSIC) has identified essential mechanisms in the immune synapse that could open up new therapeutic avenues, not only to treat autoimmune diseases, but also to enhance the response of T lymphocytes against cancer.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The human immune system is composed of a wide variety of specialized cells, with T cells playing a crucial role. Their activation is initiated when the antigen receptor on T cells recognizes and binds to antigens presented by specialized cells called antigen-presenting cells, a process that triggers the formation of the immune synapse. This phenomenon is characterized by the reorganization of signaling molecules and adhesion receptors at the site of contact, which facilitates a targeted secretion toward the antigen-presenting cell.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Actin filaments (F-actin) are essential elements in the creation and restructuring of the immune synapse. These filaments facilitate communication between T lymphocytes and antigen-presenting cells. In this process, proteins called formins play a key role, as they contribute to the reorganization of the actin cytoskeleton during T lymphocyte activation, explains Javier Ruiz-Navarro, first author of the study.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Formins and polarized secretion at the immune synapse", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "In particular, certain formins, such as Dia1 and FMNL1, are essential in targeting the T cell secretory machinery towards the immune synapse. However, the molecular mechanisms that regulate this polarized secretion have not been fully understood until now. ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The research has shown that the  isoform of FMNL1 is transiently recruited to the immune synapse following activation of the T cell antigen receptor, in a process independent of the phosphorylation of the amino acid S1086.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Once in the synapse, the phosphorylation of the FMNL1  isoform at S1086 is crucial for two functions: the reorganization of cortical F-actin and the polarization of the T cell secretory machinery towards the immune synapse. These two processes act in a coordinated manner to control the focused secretion of exosomes in the synapse, explains Ruiz-Navarro.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The study, published in eLife , was led by the teams of Manuel Izquierdo, Vctor Calvo and Francesc Garca-Gonzalo from the Sols-Morreale Biomedical Research Institute (IIBM), a joint centre of the CSIC and the UAM, and included the collaboration of researchers from IdiPAZ, CNIO and ISCIII.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Video resource", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://dauam-my.sharepoint.com/:v:/g/personal/manuel_izquierdo_inv_uam_es/Ef7EeR1IT3NJiIqIYxh-LhwB2ETcH57NZ1n9YIiW6-u5VA", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Formation of immune synapses and polarized trafficking of multivesicular bodies (MVB) to the synapse . ", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Jurkat C3 T cell clone cells expressing GFP-CD63 (green) in vesicles (CD63 is a marker of multivesicular bodies-MVBs, which are responsible for exosome release) were mixed with CMAC-labeled Raji antigen-presenting cells (blue) pulsed with staphylococcal enterotoxin E (SEE), previously bound to slides, to induce immune synapse formation. The formation of synaptic contacts between both cell types was then recorded by fluorescence microscopy. The video (7 frames per second) shows one established synapse (center) and two emerging synapses (center left and top right), together with the movement of MVBs (green GFP-CD63+ vesicles) within Jurkat cells, towards the synaptic contact zones with the blue Raji cells. Merged CMAC (blue) and GFP-CD63 (green) channels are shown. In the first frames, the entire cell surface of Jurkat cells is labeled with GFP-CD63, due to the prior, multidirectional fusion of GFP-CD63+ MVBs with the plasma membrane.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "_____________________", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Bibliographic reference:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Javier Ruiz-Navarro, Sara Fernandez-Hermira, Irene Sanz-Fernandez, Pablo Barbeito, Alfonso Navarro-Zapata, Antonio Perez-Martinez, Francesc R Garcia-Gonzalo, Victor Calvo, Manuel Izquierdo Pastor (2024). Formin-like 1 phosphorylation at S1086 is necessary for secretory polarized traffic of exosomes at the immune synapse in Jurkat T lymphocytes, eLife 13:RP96942. ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://doi.org/10.7554/eLife.96942.4", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "https://doi.org/10.7554/eLife.96942.4 ", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "More scientific culture in  ", "type": "text"}, {"bold": true, "text": "UAM Gazette", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "      ", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-27 18:25:24.896	2024-11-27 18:25:24.896	\N	1	1	en	image text
