172	whhqsqp1rjuqonkfm0b1pddo	A team of UAM students wins the overall final of the 'European Law Moot Court Competition' in Luxembourg 	The litigation team was made up of four students from the Faculty of Law: Alejandro de la Fuente Garca, Francisco Romero Brenlla, Jos Campuzano Prez and Jess Peregrina Legido. This is the first time that a team from a Spanish university has won the overall final of this competition.	2024-04-16	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "A team of four students from the UAM Faculty of Law has been declared the winner of the overall final of the 'European Law Moot Court Competition', held on April 12 in the Grand Chamber of the Court of Justice of the European Union in Luxembourg. ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "From left to right, Francisco Romero, Lars Bay-Larsen (Vice-President of the CJEU), Alejandro de la Fuente, Jos Campuzano, Jess Peregrina and Javier Dez-Hochleitner.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The UAM litigation team was made up of two students from the Law degree, Alejandro de la Fuente Garca and Francisco Romero Brenlla, and two from the Double Degree in Law and Business Administration, Jos Campuzano Prez and Jess Peregrina Legido. They were supervised by professors Nuria Bermejo and Javier Dez-Hochleitner and had as coach Rosa Cantarero Garca, a former student of the Double Degree in Law and Business Administration and a practising lawyer. Professor Carmen Martnez Capdevila also joined the team to prepare for the grand final.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "In the semi-finals, our students beat the team from Maastricht University and, in the final, the team from Roma Tre University. These teams, together with the City University of London, were the winners of their respective regional finals.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Ninety teams in competition", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Ninety teams from the United States and the EU have participated in this edition of the competition, an international competition that, through participation in a mock trial, rewards the best law students in the European Union. Organised annually by the ELMC Society and sponsored by the Court of Justice of the EU, it is considered the most prestigious competition in the field of Union law and one of the most important in the world in its category . Students litigate in English and French, which increases the level of demand and difficulty of the competition.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "This is the first time that a team from a Spanish university has won the final of this competition . In 2018, the UAM team, which included Rosa Cantarero, was the first Spanish team to reach this final, in which it was a semi-finalist, and in 2023 the UAM team was proclaimed runner-up. Our teams have also achieved other achievements such as being runner-up in the regional final in Ljubljana (2019), and the award for the best written claims and responses submitted to the competition (2020). All of them have been supervised by professors Dez-Hochleitner and Bermejo.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The team made up of Alejandro, Francisco, Jos and Jess qualified for the final after winning the regional final in Vienna last February. They reached this regional final after passing the written phase in which more than eighty teams from around the world participated. To be crowned champions of the regional final, they had to overcome five rounds and eliminated teams from prestigious universities. In particular, in the semi-finals they beat the team from the University of Leuven (Belgium) and in the final they beat the team from the University of Turin (Italy).", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Moot courts at UAM", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The UAM Faculty of Law has made a strong commitment to offering its students the opportunity to participate in Moot Courts, national and international competitions consisting of simulations of processes in which a case is resolved before a judicial body of the highest level.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "According to the Faculty itself, \\"participation in these competitions, in addition to providing students with a clear complement to their legal training, allows them to acquire a set of transversal skills and competencies that will be very useful for their future professional life (such as writing documents, legal argumentation, rhetoric, language practice, time management or teamwork, among many others)\\".", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "More information", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Share on:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-21 11:45:09.628	2024-11-27 18:48:51.152	2024-11-27 18:48:51.174	2	1	en	From left to right, Francisco Romero Brenlla, Alejandro de la Fuente Garca, Jess Peregrina Legido and Jos Campuzano Prez
92	tlkcj41rq11h6pzxeq46i4wd	'OncoTailor', 'Hive', 'SnapEAT' and 'BarberIA', finalists of the 'Pitch Day' of the UAM Emprende Prototype Program	Eight teams participating in the UAM Emprende Prototype Program for students presented their innovative ideas on June 13 at the Auditorium of Pavilion C of the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM). Of these, four made it to the finals that allow them to enter the project incubator.	2024-05-19	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "On June 13, the Auditorium of Pavilion C of the Autonomous University of Madrid hosted the Pitch Day of the UAM Emprende Prototype Program for students, in which OncoTailor, Hive, SnapEAT and BarberIA qualified as finalists and moved on to the project incubator.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "This program, Prototype, aims to identify, define and validate business proposals for projects presented by the community of the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM) through a prototype.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "A total of eight teams of entrepreneurs presented their innovative ideas to a panel of investors and entrepreneurs composed of Leticia Raya, accelerator manager at PwC and member of the Advisory Board of the International Startup Congress in Spain; Carlos Benedito, creator of content, brand and design; Patrick Christian Alain Perrodo, general manager of Crea Activitum R&D Co; Juan Martn Sainz de Vicua, chief of staff at Wavveup; Ismael Teijn, CEO of Let's WoW; Carlos Ortiz, founder of Aloha Poke; and Jorge lvarez Cercadillo, head of UAM Emprende.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The participants presented their innovative ideas for four minutes, which the jury scored through questions with the aim of awarding, at the end of the event, four teams with a pass to the project incubator.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The first round was for SuccesStart with its project to help the productivity of ICT and insurance companies, sectors where most sick leave occurs due to mental illness, with outdoor activities and psychological counselling.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The second team to present was PockAd , presenting an app where young people with social and ecological awareness could earn money by watching videos of sustainable brands.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The third team was Junior Empresa, from the UAM, which seeks to help SMEs internationalize through a team made up of university students.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The fourth team, BarberIA, has an app with Artificial Intelligence (AI) where barbershop users can schedule their appointments, as well as try out how a makeover would look on them before doing it.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "After them, SnapEAT was presented , a team working on an application where, through photographs of your food, the nutritional contribution of each food you eat is analyzed. Next, it was the turn of HIVE , a platform powered by an AI trained to help student exchange students in their study process in a foreign country.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "In penultimate place was OncoTailor, a tool for perso