e de honor de la Academia de Ciencias, Artes y Letras (Jakiunde) y presidente del jurado del premio Princesa de Asturias de Investigacin Cientfica y Tcnica desde 2012. Fue consejero del Gobierno Vasco (1980-1984), profesor visitante en el Cavendish Laboratory de Cambridge (1984-1986), miembro del consejo rector del Consejo Superior de Investigaciones Cientficas (CSIC) (2001-2007) y presidente del Centro CIC-Nanogune (2006-2019). El profesor Echenique es licenciado en Ciencias Fsicas por la Universidad de Navarra (UN) (1972), PhD por la Universidad de Cambridge (1976) y doctor en Ciencias Fsicas por la Universidad Autnoma de Barcelona (UAB) (1977). Su trayectoria cientfica es de reconocida excelencia internacional y abarca los campos de la Fsica de Superficies, la Microscopa Electrnica, el estudio de la Interaccin de Cargas y Radiacin con la Materia y, ms recientemente, la Attofsica. Ha publicado ms de 450 trabajos en libros y revistas especializadas, recibiendo ms de 28.000 citas, siendo su ndice H de 82. Ha dirigido 27 tesis doctorales y supervisado el trabajo posdoctoral de ms de 50 investigadores.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Entre las mltiples distinciones que ha recibido durante su carrera destacan el Premio Prncipe de Asturias de Investigacin Cientfico-Tcnica (1998), Max Planck Physics Prize (1998), Premio Nacional Blas Cabrera de Ciencias Fsicas, de los Materiales y de la Tierra (2005), Premio Dupont de Ciencia (1996), Premio Euskadi de Investigacin (1996), Premio Prncipe de Viana de la Cultura (1998), Gran Cruz de Alfonso X el Sabio (1998) y la Medalla de Oro de la Real Sociedad Espaola de Fsica (2003). Es miembro de la Asociacin Americana para el Avance de las Ciencias (2001), miembro extranjero de la Academia de Ciencias, Letras y Bellas Artes de Blgica (2009), as como acadmico numerario de la Real Academia de Ciencias Exactas, Fsicas y Naturales de Espaa (2014) y miembro honorario de la European Physical Society (2018). Tambin cabe destacar su labor de catalizador en la creacin de nuevos centros de investigacin en la UPV en San Sebastin: el Donostia International Physics Center (1999), el centro CIC-Nanogune (2006), y el Materials Physics Center (2009).", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Compartir en:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-21 11:55:31.377	2024-11-26 19:18:51.83	2024-11-26 19:18:51.85	2	1	es	\N
106	mrog3oxx441j9tbhw9qt376t	Watch the investiture ceremony of professors Eugenio Coronado and Pedro Miguel Echenique as honorary doctors live	Today, Thursday 25 April at 11am in the Plaza Mayor Building on the Cantoblanco Campus, the Investiture Ceremony as honorary doctors of Professors Eugenio Coronado and Pedro Miguel Echenique will be held. It can be followed live on the UAM YouTube channel.	2024-04-19	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Rector Amaya Mendikoetxea will preside over the investiture ceremony of Professors Eugenio Coronado and Pedro Miguel Echenique as honorary doctors at an event that will take place on April 25 at 11 a.m. in the Plaza Mayor Building on the Cantoblanco Campus . The event can be followed live on the UAM YouTube channel .  ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Professor Coronado , professor of Inorganic Chemistry at the University of Valencia (UV) since 1993 and director of the Institute of Molecular Science (ICMol) since its foundation in 2000, will receive an honorary doctorate at the initiative of the Department of Organic Chemistry of the Faculty of Sciences of the UAM \\"for his relevant and innovative contributions in the field of molecular magnetism, molecular materials and molecular nanotechnology, as well as for his pioneering efforts to create an interdisciplinary community in these areas worldwide\\" and his sponsor will be Professor Toms Torres Cebada.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Professor Echenique, who is currently a professor of Condensed Matter Physics at the University of the Basque Country (UPV) and president of the Donostia International Physics Center (DIPC), will receive an honorary doctorate at the initiative of the Department of Theoretical Condensed Matter Physics \\"for his excellent academic career of recognized international prestige, for his commitment, identification and promotion of the values that the UAM represents and disseminates and for the close and fruitful ties with our university over the last four decades.\\" His sponsor will be Professor Fernando Flores Sintas.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Trajectories", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Eugenio Coronado (Valencia, 1959) is, in addition to the positions mentioned above, director of the European Institute of Molecular Magnetism (EIMM), created in 2008. His research interests lie in the areas of Molecular Magnetism, Multifunctional Molecular Materials and Polyoxometalate Chemistry. For more than 25 years he has been at the forefront of these areas making fundamental contributions. More recently, his research interest has evolved towards Molecular Spintronics, which led him to receive in 2009 an Advanced Grant from the European Research Council (ERC) to work on the project Magnetic Molecules and Hybrid Materials for Molecular Spintronics, SPINMOL and the COST Action MOLSPIN (in 2016). For his study Molecular-induced control of 2D materials (MOL-2D) he received a second ERC Advanced Grant . Throughout his career, he has stimulated the creation of interdisciplinary scientific communities through the organization of collaborative networks and schools, such as the National Schools of Molecular Materials (1992) and the European Schools of Molecular Nanoscience (ESMOLNA) (2008). This research career has been recognized with several awards, both in Spain and abroad: the Rey Jaime I Prize for New Technologies (2003), the Prize and Medal for Chemical Research of the Royal Spanish Society of Chemistry (2009), the Enrique Moles National Prize for Research in Chemical Sciences (2009) and the Medal of the Royal Spanish Society of Physics (2019). He has been a member of the Academia Europaea since 2009. In 2020 he received a Humboldt Prize and in 2014 a Blaise Pascal International Chair.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Pedro Miguel Echenique (Isaba, Navarra, 1950) is also president of the Board of Partners of the Materials Physics Center (MPC), honorary president of the Academy of Sciences, Arts and Letters ( Jakiunde) and president of the jury of the Princess of Asturias Award for Technical and Scientific Research since 2012. He was an advisor to the Basque Government (1980-1984), visiting professor at the Cavendish Laboratory in Cambridge (1984-1986), member of the governing council of the Spanish National Research Council (CSIC) (2001-2007) and president of the CIC-Nanogune Center (2006-2019). Professor Echenique holds a degree in Physics from the University of Navarra (UN) (1972), a PhD from the University of Cambridge (1976) and a PhD in Physics from the Autonomous University of Barcelona (UAB) (1977). His scientific career is one of internationally recognised excellence and covers the fields of Surface Physics, Electron Microscopy, the study of the Interaction of Charges and Radiation with Matter and, more recently, Attophysics. He has published more than 450 works in books and specialist journals, receiving more than 28,000 citations, and his H index being 82. He has directed 27 doctoral theses and supervised the postdoctoral work of more than 50 researchers.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Among the many awards he has received during his career are the Prince of Asturias Award for Scientific and Technical Research (1998), the Max Planck Physics Prize (1998), the Blas Cabrera National Prize for Physical, Materials and Earth Sciences (2005), the Dupont Prize for Science (1996), the Euskadi Prize for Research (1996), the Prince of Viana Award for Culture (1998), the Grand Cross of Alfonso X the Wise (1998) and the Gold Medal of the Royal Spanish Society of Physics (2003). He is a member of the American Association for the Advancement of Science (2001), a foreign member of the Academy of Sciences, Letters and Fine Arts of Belgium (2009), as well as a full academician of the Royal Academy of Exact, Physical and Natural Sciences of Spain (2014) and an honorary member of the European Physical Society (2018). Also worth highlighting is his work as a catalyst in the creation of new research centres at the UPV in San Sebastin: the Donostia International Physics Center (1999), the CIC-Nanogune centre (2006), and the Materials Physics Center (2009).", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-21 11:56:57.614	2024-11-26 19:19:26.824	2024-11-26 19:19:26.84	2	1	en	\N
109	s4kidx45saeawotwfzn4fnge	13 ttulos de la UAM destacan en el Ranking de Mejores Msteres de El Mundo 2024	El Ranking de Mejores Msteres de El Mundo recientemente publicado destaca 13 ttulos de posgrado que se imparten en la UAM. Los msteres ms sobresalientes en la clasificacin pertenecen a las reas de Ciencia y Tecnologa (Biomolculas y Dinmica Celular), Humanidades (Historia del Arte Contemporneo y Cultura Visual) y Salud (Ciencias Forenses, Psicologa). Todos estos ttulos forman parte de la amplia oferta de msteres de la Autnoma de Madrid y hasta el prximo 2 de septiembre est abierto el segundo plazo de admisin. Toda la informacin, en el Centro de Estudios de Posgrado.	2024-05-21	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Un total de 13 ttulos impartidos por la Universidad Autnoma de Madrid (UAM) destacan en la nueva edicin del Ranking de Mejores Msteres de El Mundo publicada ayer. Del total destacados a nivel nacional, 7 ttulos son propios y otros 6 se llevan a cabo en colaboracin con otras instituciones y centros.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "La clasificacin que anualmente publica este medio, elige a los cinco mejores ttulos de cada una de las 50 especialidades analizadas, agrupados por reas de conocimiento y destaca los mejores centros en los que pueden cursarse estudios relacionados con esas disciplinas.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "La metodologa consta de 25 criterios de seleccin que valoran, entre otros aspectos, demanda del mster, recursos humanos, planes de estudio, resultados y medios materiales. Asimismo, recogen la valoracin de ms de 800 expertos, personal docente, estudiantes, antiguos alumnos y responsables empresariales.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Los msteres de la UAM clasificados entre los top 5 de cada rea de conocimiento en este ranking son:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "REA DE CIENCIA Y TECNOLOGA