114	zzgla8ezz47iv28c27jj4ekh	UAM Civil Law Professor Ignacio Garrote Fernndez-Dez, winner of the XI Antonio Delgado Prize	On the occasion of World Intellectual Property Day, which is celebrated on April 26, the Instituto Autor has recognized the study 'The special regime of civil liability of providers for sharing online content for infringement of intellectual property rights' as the winner of the XI Antonio Delgado Award. Its author is Ignacio Garrote Fernndez-Dez, professor of Civil Law at the UAM. This annual award recognizes research work on copyright and related rights.	2024-05-07	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The winning study of the 11th edition of the Antonio Delgado Award convened by the Instituto Autor is the work entitled The special regime of civil liability of providers for sharing online content for infringement of intellectual property rights , by  Ignacio Garrote Fernndez-Dez, professor of Civil Law  at the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM) and co-director of the Master's Degree in Intellectual, Industrial Property and New Technologies at the UAM, with extensive training and experience in intellectual property since the beginning of his professional career, as evidenced by the subject of his doctoral thesis (with Extraordinary Award), Copyright on the Internet, directed by Professor Rodrigo Bercovitz. ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Professor Garrote has expressed his gratitude to the Instituto Autor for having won the prize, especially to Antonio Delgado, saying:  I am very pleased to have been declared the winner of the eleventh edition of the Antonio Delgado Prize, organised by the Instituto Autor. The joy I feel now is compounded by the honour of receiving a prize that bears the name of Antonio, of whom we all have such fond memories. Antonio was a pioneer in the study and defence of copyright, and I am modestly pleased to have contributed to honouring his memory through the study that has won.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The aim of the award-winning work is to delve deeper into the special liability regime that corresponds to  online content sharing service providers , that is, the platforms that allow users of their services to upload and make available to other users files containing works and services protected by intellectual property. This regime is an essential part of Directive (EU) 2019/790, on copyright and related rights in the digital single market (arts. 2 6) and 17) and also, consequently, of Royal Decree-Law 24/2021, which transposed, among others, said Directive into our legal system (arts. 66.7 and 73 of said RD-law).", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The jury for this 11th edition of the Antonio Delgado Prize was made up of three prestigious jurists specialising in intellectual property law: Lucas Blanque Rey, a lawyer for the Council of State and Partner at GC Legal; Mercedes Curto Polo, a member of the First Section of the Intellectual Property Commission; and Rafael Farias, Regional Director for Latin America and the Caribbean of the International Confederation of Societies of Authors and Composers (CISAC).", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Promotion and dissemination of the study of Intellectual Property", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The Antonio Delgado Award is an initiative of the Instituto Autor (IA), a centre created in 2005 by the Sociedad General de Autores y Editores (SGAE) to promote and disseminate the study of Intellectual Property. It consists of two categories: an award for research work on copyright and related rights, and an award for the Dissemination of Intellectual Property.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The Antonio Delgado Award seeks to honour the memory and legacy of Antonio Delgado Porras, founder of the Instituto Autor and one of the main drafters of the draft of the Intellectual Property Law of 1987. Faithful and loyal to his commitment to the development and protection of intellectual property, he dedicated his entire life to the study and research of the subject, which led him to play a very important role in the development of much of the legislation in Latin America, especially in the area of collective management.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "More information", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-21 12:05:23.301	2024-11-26 19:25:29.62	2024-11-26 19:25:29.641	2	1	en	UAM Civil Law Professor Ignacio Garrote Fernndez-Dez, winner of the XI Antonio Delgado Prize. / UAM
