116	qno7xomn7cwdmd1ztcevbk0j	The UAM Employment Forum celebrates its 20th edition with the participation of more than 75 exhibitors	Until next Friday, March 15, the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM) is holding this annual meeting on employability. An event that will allow students and recent graduates to explore professional opportunities and establish contacts with companies from various sectors, including STEM. It will be held in a hybrid format and the physical venues will be the Faculty of Economic and Business Sciences and the Higher Polytechnic School (EPS).	2024-03-11	[{"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://www.uam.es/uam/oficina-practicas-externas/empleo/foro-empleo", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "20th Employment Forum of the Autonomous University of Madrid (UAM)", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": " will take place throughout this week - until next Friday, March 15 - in a hybrid format. The most important annual event with entrepreneurship at the UAM, organized by the Vice-Rectorate for Students and Employability of the UAM, celebrates its twentieth edition, which consolidates the success of the initiative, with the participation of more than 75 public and private entities. Its stands will be installed in the halls of the ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://www.uam.es/Economicas/Home.htm", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Faculty of Business Economics", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": " and the ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://www.uam.es/ss/Satellite/EscuelaPolitecnica/es/home.htm", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Higher Polytechnic School (EPS)", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": " on March 11 and 12. In parallel, from Wednesday 13 to Friday 15, the forum will have its virtual version in which you can participate by registering ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://foroempleouam.easyvirtualfair.com/home", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "at this link", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": " .  ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Image of the XX UAM Employment Forum at the Faculty of Economics and Business. / UAM", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "During the opening day, held today, the Vice-Rector for Students and Employability Javier Oubia, the Rector's Delegate for Employability and Alumni Idoia Alarcn and the Head of Service of the Internship and Employability Office Ruth Garca Aldea, toured the facilities, accompanied, in the Faculty of Economic and Business Sciences, by the Vice-Manager of Studies Cristina Soto and the Vice-Dean of Employability Mar Alonso (in the image).", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Access ", "type": "text"}, {"bold": true, "text": "to the Employment Forum is free and open ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "to anyone who comes to the Cantoblanco Campus on March 11 and 12. However, ", "type": "text"}, {"bold": true, "text": "some activities are exclusively aimed at UAM members", "type": "text"}, {"text": " , that is, currently enrolled students and AlumniUAM members. You can consult the complete program here .", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "This forum, which includes training activities, presentations and round tables in both modalities, offers students the opportunity to establish contacts with leading employers in various sectors, especially STEM, explore employment options to start their professional career and learn about the offer of internships and programs for graduates. The meeting also allows attendees to learn about the latest trends in the labor market and strategies for conducting an effective job search.  ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Featured Activities", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Image of the XX UAM Employment Forum at the Faculty of Economics and Business. / UAM", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Among the scheduled activities is the ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://foroempleouam.easyvirtualfair.com/resources/private/documents/Cafes_con_candidatos.pdf", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Student and Graduate Caf", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": ", an opportunity to network with human resources representatives from the different entities that will participate in the Employment Forum. At this unique event, upon registration, students will be able to establish relationships with Human Resources representatives from various entities participating in the Employment Forum. This caf is intended to take place in a relaxed but professional environment, designed to foster meaningful conversations and genuine connections. At the caf, students will be able to learn about internships or job opportunities available, expand their professional networks, and enjoy a welcoming and stimulating environment in the company of other UAM students and graduates with common affinities.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Participants will also be able to participate in the practical workshop ", "type": "text"}, {"bold": true, "text": "Learn to use LinkedIn", "type": "text"}, {"text": " and take advantage of the opportunity to boost their professional career on social networks. For 50 minutes, participants will immerse themselves in the world of LinkedIn, to understand how it works, master the techniques to build a profile and maximize their presence on this platform, expand their network of contacts and define their personal brand effectively.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The session is scheduled for  ", "type": "text"}, {"bold": true, "text": "Wednesday, March 13 at 12 noon", "type": "text"}, {"text": " in the Multifunction Room of the Faculty of Economics and Business Administration. Free admission.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The UAM and employability", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Image of the XX UAM Employment Forum at the Faculty of Economics and Business. / UAM", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "The main objective of the XX Employment Forum is to promote the employability of students and graduates of the university. According to the latest data from the ", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://obs-empleabilidad.uam.es/", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "UAM Employment Observatory ", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": ", 8 out of 10 graduates of Bachelor's degrees, 9 out of 10 Master's and Own Degrees and 10 out of 10 Doctorate graduates enter the labour market. The average time of active search for recent graduates who had not previously worked is between two and three months. The data also reflect that around 80% of graduates of Bachelor's degrees, postgraduate degrees and doctorates consider that the UAM has contributed to improving their employability.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "The Forum in detail", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Date:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "March 11 and 12 from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. (in-person format). March 13, 14 and 15 ( online format ).", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Hour:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "From 10 am to 6 pm", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Place:", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "Face-to-face Employment Forum: Entrance hall to the Faculty of Economics and Business Administration and entrance hall to the Higher Polytechnic School (EPS). Cantoblanco Campus.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://foroempleouam.easyvirtualfair.com/landing", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "Virtual Employment Forum", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": "", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "children": [{"text": "", "type": "text"}, {"url": "https://www.uam.es/uam/oficina-practicas-externas/empleo/foro-empleo", "type": "link", "children": [{"bold": true, "text": "More information", "type": "text"}]}, {"text": "", "type": "text"}]}]	2024-11-18 20:50:15.931	2024-11-26 19:26:25.883	2024-11-26 19:26:25.902	1	1	en	Poster of the XX UAM Employment Forum at the Faculty of Economics and Business. / UAM
